@kelzk
Are you implying that Earthbound had less direction than most RPGs and exploring games at the time?
If you really did pay attention, you would see that most of the time, the game practically tells you where to go! There was even the hint man who would give hints on where to go next! You almost never had to guess, except for that time where you have to use the Pak of Gum to lower the rope...
